<doc id="1210504" wikidata="Q5632846" url="?curid=1210504" title="HMS Hyperion">
<text>Two ships of the Royal Navy have borne the name HMS &quot;Hyperion&quot;, after Hyperion, one of the Titans of Greek mythology. A third was planned but never completed: 

* was a 32-gun fifth rate launched in 1807 and broken up in 1833.
* HMS &quot;Hyperion&quot; was to have been a wooden screw frigate. She was ordered in 1861 and cancelled in 1863.
* was a H-class destroyer launched in 1936. She was scuttled in 1940 after being damaged by a mine.</text><links>
